20class ConstantRangeTest : public ::testing::Test {
21protected:
22 static ConstantRange Full;
23 static ConstantRange Empty;
24 static ConstantRange One;
25 static ConstantRange Some;
26 static ConstantRange Wrap;
27};

29template<typename Fn>
30static void EnumerateConstantRanges(unsigned Bits, Fn TestFn) {
31 unsigned Max = 1 << Bits;
32 for (unsigned Lo = 0; Lo < Max; Lo++) {
33 for (unsigned Hi = 0; Hi < Max; Hi++) {
34 // Enforce ConstantRange invariant.
35 if (Lo == Hi && Lo != 0 && Lo != Max - 1)
36 continue;
37
38 ConstantRange CR(APInt(Bits, Lo), APInt(Bits, Hi));
39 TestFn(CR);
40 }
41 }
42}
43
44template<typename Fn>
45static void EnumerateTwoConstantRanges(unsigned Bits, Fn TestFn) {
46 EnumerateConstantRanges(Bits, [&](const ConstantRange &CR1) {
47 EnumerateConstantRanges(Bits, [&](const ConstantRange &CR2) {
48 TestFn(CR1, CR2);
49 });
50 });
51}
52
53template<typename Fn>
54static void ForeachNumInConstantRange(const ConstantRange &CR, Fn TestFn) {
55 if (!CR.isEmptySet()) {
56 APInt N = CR.getLower();
57 do TestFn(N);
58 while (++N != CR.getUpper());
59 }
60}
61
62struct OpRangeGathererBase {
63 void account(const APInt &N);
64 ConstantRange getRange();
65};
66
67struct UnsignedOpRangeGatherer : public OpRangeGathererBase {
68 APInt Min;
69 APInt Max;
70
71 UnsignedOpRangeGatherer(unsigned Bits)
72 : Min(APInt::getMaxValue(Bits)), Max(APInt::getMinValue(Bits)) {}
73
74 void account(const APInt &N) {
75 if (N.ult(Min))
76 Min = N;
77 if (N.ugt(Max))
78 Max = N;
79 }
80
81 ConstantRange getRange() {
82 if (Min.ugt(Max))
83 return ConstantRange::getEmpty(Min.getBitWidth());
84 return ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(Min, Max + 1);
85 }
86};
87
88struct SignedOpRangeGatherer : public OpRangeGathererBase {
89 APInt Min;
90 APInt Max;
91
92 SignedOpRangeGatherer(unsigned Bits)
93 : Min(APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Bits)),
94 Max(APInt::getSignedMinValue(Bits)) {}
95
96 void account(const APInt &N) {
97 if (N.slt(Min))
98 Min = N;
99 if (N.sgt(Max))
100 Max = N;
101 }
102
103 ConstantRange getRange() {
104 if (Min.sgt(Max))
105 return ConstantRange::getEmpty(Min.getBitWidth());
106 return ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(Min, Max + 1);
107 }
108};
109
110template <typename Fn1, typename Fn2>
111static void TestUnsignedUnaryOpExhaustive(Fn1 RangeFn, Fn2 IntFn,
112 bool SkipSignedIntMin = false) {
113 unsigned Bits = 4;
114 EnumerateConstantRanges(Bits, [&](const ConstantRange &CR) {
115 UnsignedOpRangeGatherer R(CR.getBitWidth());
116 ForeachNumInConstantRange(CR, [&](const APInt &N) {
117 if (SkipSignedIntMin && N.isMinSignedValue())
118 return;
119 R.account(IntFn(N));
120 });
121
122 ConstantRange ExactCR = R.getRange();
123 ConstantRange ActualCR = RangeFn(CR);
124
125 EXPECT_EQ(ExactCR, ActualCR);
126 });
127}
128
129template <typename Fn1, typename Fn2>
130static void TestUnsignedBinOpExhaustive(Fn1 RangeFn, Fn2 IntFn,
131 bool SkipZeroRHS = false,
132 bool CorrectnessOnly = false) {
133 unsigned Bits = 4;
134 EnumerateTwoConstantRanges(
135 Bits, [&](const ConstantRange &CR1, const ConstantRange &CR2) {
136 UnsignedOpRangeGatherer R(CR1.getBitWidth());
137 ForeachNumInConstantRange(CR1, [&](const APInt &N1) {
138 ForeachNumInConstantRange(CR2, [&](const APInt &N2) {
139 if (SkipZeroRHS && N2 == 0)
140 return;
141 R.account(IntFn(N1, N2));
142 });
143 });
144
145 ConstantRange CR = RangeFn(CR1, CR2);
146
147 ConstantRange Exact = R.getRange();
148
149 if (!CorrectnessOnly) {
150 EXPECT_EQ(Exact, CR);
151 return;
152 }
153
154 EXPECT_TRUE(CR.contains(Exact));
155 if (Exact.isEmptySet()) {
156 EXPECT_TRUE(CR.isEmptySet());
157 }
158 });
159}
160
161template <typename Fn1, typename Fn2>
162static void TestSignedBinOpExhaustive(Fn1 RangeFn, Fn2 IntFn,
163 bool SkipZeroRHS = false,
164 bool CorrectnessOnly = false) {
165 unsigned Bits = 4;
166 EnumerateTwoConstantRanges(
167 Bits, [&](const ConstantRange &CR1, const ConstantRange &CR2) {
168 SignedOpRangeGatherer R(CR1.getBitWidth());
169 ForeachNumInConstantRange(CR1, [&](const APInt &N1) {
170 ForeachNumInConstantRange(CR2, [&](const APInt &N2) {
171 if (SkipZeroRHS && N2 == 0)
172 return;
173
174 R.account(IntFn(N1, N2));
175 });
176 });
177
178 ConstantRange CR = RangeFn(CR1, CR2);
179
180 ConstantRange Exact = R.getRange();
181 if (CorrectnessOnly) {
182 EXPECT_TRUE(CR.contains(Exact));
183 } else {
184 EXPECT_EQ(Exact, CR);
185 }
186 });
187}

189ConstantRange ConstantRangeTest::Full(16, true);
190ConstantRange ConstantRangeTest::Empty(16, false);
191ConstantRange ConstantRangeTest::One(APInt(16, 0xa));
192ConstantRange ConstantRangeTest::Some(APInt(16, 0xa), APInt(16, 0xaaa));
193ConstantRange ConstantRangeTest::Wrap(APInt(16, 0xaaa), APInt(16, 0xa));

195TEST_F(ConstantRangeTest, Basics) {
196 EXPECT_TRUE(Full.isFullSet());
197 EXPECT_FALSE(Full.isEmptySet());
198 EXPECT_TRUE(Full.inverse().isEmptySet());
199 EXPECT_FALSE(Full.isWrappedSet());
200 EXPECT_TRUE(Full.contains(APInt(16, 0x0)));
201 EXPECT_TRUE(Full.contains(APInt(16, 0x9)));
202 EXPECT_TRUE(Full.contains(APInt(16, 0xa)));
203 EXPECT_TRUE(Full.contains(APInt(16, 0xaa9)));
204 EXPECT_TRUE(Full.contains(APInt(16, 0xaaa)));
205
206 EXPECT_FALSE(Empty.isFullSet());
207 EXPECT_TRUE(Empty.isEmptySet());
208 EXPECT_TRUE(Empty.inverse().isFullSet());
209 EXPECT_FALSE(Empty.isWrappedSet());
210 EXPECT_FALSE(Empty.contains(APInt(16, 0x0)));
211 EXPECT_FALSE(Empty.contains(APInt(16, 0x9)));
212 EXPECT_FALSE(Empty.contains(APInt(16, 0xa)));
213 EXPECT_FALSE(Empty.contains(APInt(16, 0xaa9)));
214 EXPECT_FALSE(Empty.contains(APInt(16, 0xaaa)));
215
216 EXPECT_FALSE(One.isFullSet());
217 EXPECT_FALSE(One.isEmptySet());
218 EXPECT_FALSE(One.isWrappedSet());
219 EXPECT_FALSE(One.contains(APInt(16, 0x0)));
220 EXPECT_FALSE(One.contains(APInt(16, 0x9)));
221 EXPECT_TRUE(One.contains(APInt(16, 0xa)));
222 EXPECT_FALSE(One.contains(APInt(16, 0xaa9)));
223 EXPECT_FALSE(One.contains(APInt(16, 0xaaa)));
224 EXPECT_FALSE(One.inverse().contains(APInt(16, 0xa)));
225
226 EXPECT_FALSE(Some.isFullSet());
227 EXPECT_FALSE(Some.isEmptySet());
228 EXPECT_FALSE(Some.isWrappedSet());
229 EXPECT_FALSE(Some.contains(APInt(16, 0x0)));
230 EXPECT_FALSE(Some.contains(APInt(16, 0x9)));
231 EXPECT_TRUE(Some.contains(APInt(16, 0xa)));
232 EXPECT_TRUE(Some.contains(APInt(16, 0xaa9)));
233 EXPECT_FALSE(Some.contains(APInt(16, 0xaaa)));
234
235 EXPECT_FALSE(Wrap.isFullSet());
236 EXPECT_FALSE(Wrap.isEmptySet());
237 EXPECT_TRUE(Wrap.isWrappedSet());
238 EXPECT_TRUE(Wrap.contains(APInt(16, 0x0)));
239 EXPECT_TRUE(Wrap.contains(APInt(16, 0x9)));
240 EXPECT_FALSE(Wrap.contains(APInt(16, 0xa)));
241 EXPECT_FALSE(Wrap.contains(APInt(16, 0xaa9)));
242 EXPECT_TRUE(Wrap.contains(APInt(16, 0xaaa)));
243}

245TEST_F(ConstantRangeTest, Equality) {
246 EXPECT_EQ(Full, Full);
247 EXPECT_EQ(Empty, Empty);
248 EXPECT_EQ(One, One);
249 EXPECT_EQ(Some, Some);
250 EXPECT_EQ(Wrap, Wrap);
251 EXPECT_NE(Full, Empty);
252 EXPECT_NE(Full, One);
253 EXPECT_NE(Full, Some);
254 EXPECT_NE(Full, Wrap);
255 EXPECT_NE(Empty, One);
256 EXPECT_NE(Empty, Some);
257 EXPECT_NE(Empty, Wrap);
258 EXPECT_NE(One, Some);
259 EXPECT_NE(One, Wrap);
260 EXPECT_NE(Some, Wrap);
261}

263TEST_F(ConstantRangeTest, SingleElement) {
264 EXPECT_EQ(Full.getSingleElement(), static_cast<APInt *>(nullptr));
265 EXPECT_EQ(Empty.getSingleElement(), static_cast<APInt *>(nullptr));
266 EXPECT_EQ(Full.getSingleMissingElement(), static_cast<APInt *>(nullptr));
267 EXPECT_EQ(Empty.getSingleMissingElement(), static_cast<APInt *>(nullptr));
268
269 EXPECT_EQ(*One.getSingleElement(), APInt(16, 0xa));
270 EXPECT_EQ(Some.getSingleElement(), static_cast<APInt *>(nullptr));
271 EXPECT_EQ(Wrap.getSingleElement(), static_cast<APInt *>(nullptr));
272
273 EXPECT_EQ(One.getSingleMissingElement(), static_cast<APInt *>(nullptr));
274 EXPECT_EQ(Some.getSingleMissingElement(), static_cast<APInt *>(nullptr));
275
276 ConstantRange OneInverse = One.inverse();
277 EXPECT_EQ(*OneInverse.getSingleMissingElement(), *One.getSingleElement());
278
279 EXPECT_FALSE(Full.isSingleElement());
280 EXPECT_FALSE(Empty.isSingleElement());
281 EXPECT_TRUE(One.isSingleElement());
282 EXPECT_FALSE(Some.isSingleElement());
283 EXPECT_FALSE(Wrap.isSingleElement());
284}

286TEST_F(ConstantRangeTest, GetMinsAndMaxes) {
287 EXPECT_EQ(Full.getUnsignedMax(), APInt(16, UINT16_MAX));
288 EXPECT_EQ(One.getUnsignedMax(), APInt(16, 0xa));
289 EXPECT_EQ(Some.getUnsignedMax(), APInt(16, 0xaa9));
290 EXPECT_EQ(Wrap.getUnsignedMax(), APInt(16, UINT16_MAX));
291
292 EXPECT_EQ(Full.getUnsignedMin(), APInt(16, 0));
293 EXPECT_EQ(One.getUnsignedMin(), APInt(16, 0xa));
294 EXPECT_EQ(Some.getUnsignedMin(), APInt(16, 0xa));
295 EXPECT_EQ(Wrap.getUnsignedMin(), APInt(16, 0));
296
297 EXPECT_EQ(Full.getSignedMax(), APInt(16, INT16_MAX));
298 EXPECT_EQ(One.getSignedMax(), APInt(16, 0xa));
299 EXPECT_EQ(Some.getSignedMax(), APInt(16, 0xaa9));
300 EXPECT_EQ(Wrap.getSignedMax(), APInt(16, INT16_MAX));
301
302 EXPECT_EQ(Full.getSignedMin(), APInt(16, (uint64_t)INT16_MIN));
303 EXPECT_EQ(One.getSignedMin(), APInt(16, 0xa));
304 EXPECT_EQ(Some.getSignedMin(), APInt(16, 0xa));

312TEST_F(ConstantRangeTest, SignWrapped) {
313 EXPECT_FALSE(Full.isSignWrappedSet());
314 EXPECT_FALSE(Empty.isSignWrappedSet());
315 EXPECT_FALSE(One.isSignWrappedSet());
316 EXPECT_FALSE(Some.isSignWrappedSet());
317 EXPECT_TRUE(Wrap.isSignWrappedSet());
318
319 EXPECT_FALSE(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 127), APInt(8, 128)).isSignWrappedSet());
320 EXPECT_TRUE(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 127), APInt(8, 129)).isSignWrappedSet());
321 EXPECT_FALSE(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 128), APInt(8, 129)).isSignWrappedSet());
322 EXPECT_TRUE(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 10), APInt(8, 9)).isSignWrappedSet());
323 EXPECT_TRUE(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 10), APInt(8, 250)).isSignWrappedSet());
324 EXPECT_FALSE(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 250), APInt(8, 10)).isSignWrappedSet());
325 EXPECT_FALSE(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 250), APInt(8, 251)).isSignWrappedSet());
326}

328TEST_F(ConstantRangeTest, UpperWrapped) {
329 // The behavior here is the same as for isWrappedSet() / isSignWrappedSet().
330 EXPECT_FALSE(Full.isUpperWrapped());
331 EXPECT_FALSE(Empty.isUpperWrapped());
332 EXPECT_FALSE(One.isUpperWrapped());
333 EXPECT_FALSE(Some.isUpperWrapped());
334 EXPECT_TRUE(Wrap.isUpperWrapped());
335 EXPECT_FALSE(Full.isUpperSignWrapped());
336 EXPECT_FALSE(Empty.isUpperSignWrapped());
337 EXPECT_FALSE(One.isUpperSignWrapped());
338 EXPECT_FALSE(Some.isUpperSignWrapped());
339 EXPECT_TRUE(Wrap.isUpperSignWrapped());
340
341 // The behavior differs if Upper is the Min/SignedMin value.
342 ConstantRange CR1(APInt(8, 42), APInt::getMinValue(8));
343 EXPECT_FALSE(CR1.isWrappedSet());
344 EXPECT_TRUE(CR1.isUpperWrapped());
345
346 ConstantRange CR2(APInt(8, 42), APInt::getSignedMinValue(8));
347 EXPECT_FALSE(CR2.isSignWrappedSet());
348 EXPECT_TRUE(CR2.isUpperSignWrapped());
349}

351TEST_F(ConstantRangeTest, Trunc) {
352 ConstantRange TFull = Full.truncate(10);
353 ConstantRange TEmpty = Empty.truncate(10);
354 ConstantRange TOne = One.truncate(10);
355 ConstantRange TSome = Some.truncate(10);
356 ConstantRange TWrap = Wrap.truncate(10);
357 EXPECT_TRUE(TFull.isFullSet());
358 EXPECT_TRUE(TEmpty.isEmptySet());
359 EXPECT_EQ(TOne, ConstantRange(One.getLower().trunc(10),
360 One.getUpper().trunc(10)));
361 EXPECT_TRUE(TSome.isFullSet());
362 EXPECT_TRUE(TWrap.isFullSet());
363
364 // trunc([2, 5), 3->2) = [2, 1)
365 ConstantRange TwoFive(APInt(3, 2), APInt(3, 5));
366 EXPECT_EQ(TwoFive.truncate(2), ConstantRange(APInt(2, 2), APInt(2, 1)));
367
368 // trunc([2, 6), 3->2) = full
369 ConstantRange TwoSix(APInt(3, 2), APInt(3, 6));
370 EXPECT_TRUE(TwoSix.truncate(2).isFullSet());
371
372 // trunc([5, 7), 3->2) = [1, 3)
373 ConstantRange FiveSeven(APInt(3, 5), APInt(3, 7));
374 EXPECT_EQ(FiveSeven.truncate(2), ConstantRange(APInt(2, 1), APInt(2, 3)));
375
376 // trunc([7, 1), 3->2) = [3, 1)
377 ConstantRange SevenOne(APInt(3, 7), APInt(3, 1));
378 EXPECT_EQ(SevenOne.truncate(2), ConstantRange(APInt(2, 3), APInt(2, 1)));
379}

382 ConstantRange ZFull = Full.zeroExtend(20);
383 ConstantRange ZEmpty = Empty.zeroExtend(20);
384 ConstantRange ZOne = One.zeroExtend(20);
385 ConstantRange ZSome = Some.zeroExtend(20);
386 ConstantRange ZWrap = Wrap.zeroExtend(20);
387 EXPECT_EQ(ZFull, ConstantRange(APInt(20, 0), APInt(20, 0x10000)));

389 EXPECT_EQ(ZOne, ConstantRange(One.getLower().zext(20),
390 One.getUpper().zext(20)));
391 EXPECT_EQ(ZSome, ConstantRange(Some.getLower().zext(20),
392 Some.getUpper().zext(20)));
393 EXPECT_EQ(ZWrap, ConstantRange(APInt(20, 0), APInt(20, 0x10000)));
394
395 // zext([5, 0), 3->7) = [5, 8)
396 ConstantRange FiveZero(APInt(3, 5), APInt(3, 0));
397 EXPECT_EQ(FiveZero.zeroExtend(7), ConstantRange(APInt(7, 5), APInt(7, 8)));
398}

417 ConstantRange(APInt(16, -128), APInt(16, 128)));
418
419 EXPECT_EQ(ConstantRange(APInt(16, 0x0200), APInt(16, 0x8000)).signExtend(19),
420 ConstantRange(APInt(19, 0x0200), APInt(19, 0x8000)));

423TEST_F(ConstantRangeTest, IntersectWith) {
424 EXPECT_EQ(Empty.intersectWith(Full), Empty);
425 EXPECT_EQ(Empty.intersectWith(Empty), Empty);
426 EXPECT_EQ(Empty.intersectWith(One), Empty);
427 EXPECT_EQ(Empty.intersectWith(Some), Empty);
428 EXPECT_EQ(Empty.intersectWith(Wrap), Empty);
429 EXPECT_EQ(Full.intersectWith(Full), Full);
430 EXPECT_EQ(Some.intersectWith(Some), Some);
431 EXPECT_EQ(Some.intersectWith(One), One);
432 EXPECT_EQ(Full.intersectWith(One), One);
433 EXPECT_EQ(Full.intersectWith(Some), Some);
434 EXPECT_EQ(Some.intersectWith(Wrap), Empty);
435 EXPECT_EQ(One.intersectWith(Wrap), Empty);
436 EXPECT_EQ(One.intersectWith(Wrap), Wrap.intersectWith(One));
437
438 // Klee generated testcase from PR4545.
439 // The intersection of i16 [4, 2) and [6, 5) is disjoint, looking like
440 // 01..4.6789ABCDEF where the dots represent values not in the intersection.
441 ConstantRange LHS(APInt(16, 4), APInt(16, 2));
442 ConstantRange RHS(APInt(16, 6), APInt(16, 5));
443 EXPECT_TRUE(LHS.intersectWith(RHS) == LHS);
444
445 // previous bug: intersection of [min, 3) and [2, max) should be 2
446 LHS = ConstantRange(APInt(32, -2147483646), APInt(32, 3));
447 RHS = ConstantRange(APInt(32, 2), APInt(32, 2147483646));
448 EXPECT_EQ(LHS.intersectWith(RHS), ConstantRange(APInt(32, 2)));
449
450 // [2, 0) /\ [4, 3) = [2, 0)
451 LHS = ConstantRange(APInt(32, 2), APInt(32, 0));
452 RHS = ConstantRange(APInt(32, 4), APInt(32, 3));
453 EXPECT_EQ(LHS.intersectWith(RHS), ConstantRange(APInt(32, 2), APInt(32, 0)));
454
455 // [2, 0) /\ [4, 2) = [4, 0)
456 LHS = ConstantRange(APInt(32, 2), APInt(32, 0));
457 RHS = ConstantRange(APInt(32, 4), APInt(32, 2));
458 EXPECT_EQ(LHS.intersectWith(RHS), ConstantRange(APInt(32, 4), APInt(32, 0)));
459
460 // [4, 2) /\ [5, 1) = [5, 1)
461 LHS = ConstantRange(APInt(32, 4), APInt(32, 2));
462 RHS = ConstantRange(APInt(32, 5), APInt(32, 1));
463 EXPECT_EQ(LHS.intersectWith(RHS), ConstantRange(APInt(32, 5), APInt(32, 1)));
464
465 // [2, 0) /\ [7, 4) = [7, 4)
466 LHS = ConstantRange(APInt(32, 2), APInt(32, 0));
467 RHS = ConstantRange(APInt(32, 7), APInt(32, 4));
468 EXPECT_EQ(LHS.intersectWith(RHS), ConstantRange(APInt(32, 7), APInt(32, 4)));
469
470 // [4, 2) /\ [1, 0) = [1, 0)
471 LHS = ConstantRange(APInt(32, 4), APInt(32, 2));
472 RHS = ConstantRange(APInt(32, 1), APInt(32, 0));
473 EXPECT_EQ(LHS.intersectWith(RHS), ConstantRange(APInt(32, 4), APInt(32, 2)));
474
475 // [15, 0) /\ [7, 6) = [15, 0)
476 LHS = ConstantRange(APInt(32, 15), APInt(32, 0));
477 RHS = ConstantRange(APInt(32, 7), APInt(32, 6));
478 EXPECT_EQ(LHS.intersectWith(RHS), ConstantRange(APInt(32, 15), APInt(32, 0)));
479}
480
481template<typename Fn1, typename Fn2>
482void testBinarySetOperationExhaustive(Fn1 OpFn, Fn2 InResultFn) {
483 unsigned Bits = 4;
484 EnumerateTwoConstantRanges(Bits,
485 [=](const ConstantRange &CR1, const ConstantRange &CR2) {
486 // Collect up to three contiguous unsigned ranges. The HaveInterrupt
487 // variables are used determine when we have to switch to the next
488 // range because the previous one ended.
489 APInt Lower1(Bits, 0), Upper1(Bits, 0);
490 APInt Lower2(Bits, 0), Upper2(Bits, 0);
491 APInt Lower3(Bits, 0), Upper3(Bits, 0);
492 bool HaveRange1 = false, HaveInterrupt1 = false;
493 bool HaveRange2 = false, HaveInterrupt2 = false;
494 bool HaveRange3 = false, HaveInterrupt3 = false;
495
496 APInt Num(Bits, 0);
497 for (unsigned I = 0, Limit = 1 << Bits; I < Limit; ++I, ++Num) {
498 if (!InResultFn(CR1, CR2, Num)) {
499 if (HaveRange3)
500 HaveInterrupt3 = true;
501 else if (HaveRange2)
502 HaveInterrupt2 = true;
503 else if (HaveRange1)
504 HaveInterrupt1 = true;
505 continue;
506 }
507
508 if (HaveRange3) {
509 Upper3 = Num;
510 } else if (HaveInterrupt2) {
511 HaveRange3 = true;
512 Lower3 = Upper3 = Num;
513 } else if (HaveRange2) {
514 Upper2 = Num;
515 } else if (HaveInterrupt1) {
516 HaveRange2 = true;
517 Lower2 = Upper2 = Num;
518 } else if (HaveRange1) {
519 Upper1 = Num;
520 } else {
521 HaveRange1 = true;
522 Lower1 = Upper1 = Num;
523 }
524 }
525
526 (void)HaveInterrupt3;
527 assert(!HaveInterrupt3 && "Should have at most three ranges");
528
529 ConstantRange SmallestCR = OpFn(CR1, CR2, ConstantRange::Smallest);
530 ConstantRange UnsignedCR = OpFn(CR1, CR2, ConstantRange::Unsigned);
531 ConstantRange SignedCR = OpFn(CR1, CR2, ConstantRange::Signed);
532
533 if (!HaveRange1) {
534 EXPECT_TRUE(SmallestCR.isEmptySet());
535 EXPECT_TRUE(UnsignedCR.isEmptySet());
536 EXPECT_TRUE(SignedCR.isEmptySet());
537 return;
538 }
539
540 if (!HaveRange2) {
541 if (Lower1 == Upper1 + 1) {
542 EXPECT_TRUE(SmallestCR.isFullSet());
543 EXPECT_TRUE(UnsignedCR.isFullSet());
544 EXPECT_TRUE(SignedCR.isFullSet());
545 } else {
546 ConstantRange Expected(Lower1, Upper1 + 1);
547 EXPECT_EQ(Expected, SmallestCR);
548 EXPECT_EQ(Expected, UnsignedCR);
549 EXPECT_EQ(Expected, SignedCR);
550 }
551 return;
552 }
553
554 ConstantRange Variant1(Bits, /*full*/ true);
555 ConstantRange Variant2(Bits, /*full*/ true);
556 if (!HaveRange3) {
557 // Compute the two possible ways to cover two disjoint ranges.
558 if (Lower1 != Upper2 + 1)
559 Variant1 = ConstantRange(Lower1, Upper2 + 1);
560 if (Lower2 != Upper1 + 1)
561 Variant2 = ConstantRange(Lower2, Upper1 + 1);
562 } else {
563 // If we have three ranges, the first and last one have to be adjacent
564 // to the unsigned domain. It's better to think of this as having two
565 // holes, and we can construct one range using each hole.
566 assert(Lower1.isNullValue() && Upper3.isMaxValue());
567 Variant1 = ConstantRange(Lower2, Upper1 + 1);
568 Variant2 = ConstantRange(Lower3, Upper2 + 1);
569 }
570
571 // Smallest: Smaller set, then any set.
572 if (Variant1.isSizeStrictlySmallerThan(Variant2))
573 EXPECT_EQ(Variant1, SmallestCR);
574 else if (Variant2.isSizeStrictlySmallerThan(Variant1))
575 EXPECT_EQ(Variant2, SmallestCR);
576 else
577 EXPECT_TRUE(Variant1 == SmallestCR || Variant2 == SmallestCR);
578
579 // Unsigned: Non-wrapped set, then smaller set, then any set.
580 bool Variant1Full = Variant1.isFullSet() || Variant1.isWrappedSet();
581 bool Variant2Full = Variant2.isFullSet() || Variant2.isWrappedSet();
582 if (!Variant1Full && Variant2Full)
583 EXPECT_EQ(Variant1, UnsignedCR);
584 else if (Variant1Full && !Variant2Full)
585 EXPECT_EQ(Variant2, UnsignedCR);
586 else if (Variant1.isSizeStrictlySmallerThan(Variant2))
587 EXPECT_EQ(Variant1, UnsignedCR);
588 else if (Variant2.isSizeStrictlySmallerThan(Variant1))
589 EXPECT_EQ(Variant2, UnsignedCR);
590 else
591 EXPECT_TRUE(Variant1 == UnsignedCR || Variant2 == UnsignedCR);
592
593 // Signed: Signed non-wrapped set, then smaller set, then any set.
594 Variant1Full = Variant1.isFullSet() || Variant1.isSignWrappedSet();
595 Variant2Full = Variant2.isFullSet() || Variant2.isSignWrappedSet();
596 if (!Variant1Full && Variant2Full)
597 EXPECT_EQ(Variant1, SignedCR);
598 else if (Variant1Full && !Variant2Full)
599 EXPECT_EQ(Variant2, SignedCR);
600 else if (Variant1.isSizeStrictlySmallerThan(Variant2))
601 EXPECT_EQ(Variant1, SignedCR);
602 else if (Variant2.isSizeStrictlySmallerThan(Variant1))
603 EXPECT_EQ(Variant2, SignedCR);
604 else
605 EXPECT_TRUE(Variant1 == SignedCR || Variant2 == SignedCR);
606 });
607}

692 });

752template <typename Fn1, typename Fn2>
753static void TestAddWithNoSignedWrapExhaustive(Fn1 RangeFn, Fn2 IntFn) {
754 unsigned Bits = 4;
755 EnumerateTwoConstantRanges(Bits, [&](const ConstantRange &CR1,
756 const ConstantRange &CR2) {
757 ConstantRange CR = RangeFn(CR1, CR2);
758 SignedOpRangeGatherer R(CR.getBitWidth());
759 bool AllOverflow = true;
760 ForeachNumInConstantRange(CR1, [&](const APInt &N1) {
761 ForeachNumInConstantRange(CR2, [&](const APInt &N2) {
762 bool IsOverflow = false;
763 APInt N = IntFn(IsOverflow, N1, N2);
764 if (!IsOverflow) {
765 AllOverflow = false;
766 R.account(N);
767 EXPECT_TRUE(CR.contains(N));
768 }
769 });
770 });
771
772 EXPECT_EQ(CR.isEmptySet(), AllOverflow);
773
774 if (CR1.isSignWrappedSet() || CR2.isSignWrappedSet())
775 return;
776
777 ConstantRange Exact = R.getRange();
778 EXPECT_EQ(Exact, CR);
779 });
780}
781
782template <typename Fn1, typename Fn2>
783static void TestAddWithNoUnsignedWrapExhaustive(Fn1 RangeFn, Fn2 IntFn) {
784 unsigned Bits = 4;
785 EnumerateTwoConstantRanges(Bits, [&](const ConstantRange &CR1,
786 const ConstantRange &CR2) {
787 ConstantRange CR = RangeFn(CR1, CR2);
788 UnsignedOpRangeGatherer R(CR.getBitWidth());
789 bool AllOverflow = true;
790 ForeachNumInConstantRange(CR1, [&](const APInt &N1) {
791 ForeachNumInConstantRange(CR2, [&](const APInt &N2) {
792 bool IsOverflow = false;
793 APInt N = IntFn(IsOverflow, N1, N2);
794 if (!IsOverflow) {
795 AllOverflow = false;
796 R.account(N);
797 EXPECT_TRUE(CR.contains(N));
798 }
799 });
800 });
801
802 EXPECT_EQ(CR.isEmptySet(), AllOverflow);
803
804 if (CR1.isWrappedSet() || CR2.isWrappedSet())
805 return;
806
807 ConstantRange Exact = R.getRange();
808 EXPECT_EQ(Exact, CR);
809 });
810}
811
812template <typename Fn1, typename Fn2, typename Fn3>
813static void TestAddWithNoSignedUnsignedWrapExhaustive(Fn1 RangeFn,
814 Fn2 IntFnSigned,
815 Fn3 IntFnUnsigned) {
816 unsigned Bits = 4;
817 EnumerateTwoConstantRanges(
818 Bits, [&](const ConstantRange &CR1, const ConstantRange &CR2) {
819 ConstantRange CR = RangeFn(CR1, CR2);
820 UnsignedOpRangeGatherer UR(CR.getBitWidth());
821 SignedOpRangeGatherer SR(CR.getBitWidth());
822 bool AllOverflow = true;
823 ForeachNumInConstantRange(CR1, [&](const APInt &N1) {
824 ForeachNumInConstantRange(CR2, [&](const APInt &N2) {
825 bool IsOverflow = false, IsSignedOverflow = false;
826 APInt N = IntFnSigned(IsSignedOverflow, N1, N2);
827 (void) IntFnUnsigned(IsOverflow, N1, N2);
828 if (!IsSignedOverflow && !IsOverflow) {
829 AllOverflow = false;
830 UR.account(N);
831 SR.account(N);
832 EXPECT_TRUE(CR.contains(N));
833 }
834 });
835 });
836
837 EXPECT_EQ(CR.isEmptySet(), AllOverflow);
838
839 if (CR1.isWrappedSet() || CR2.isWrappedSet() ||
840 CR1.isSignWrappedSet() || CR2.isSignWrappedSet())
841 return;
842
843 ConstantRange ExactUnsignedCR = UR.getRange();
844 ConstantRange ExactSignedCR = SR.getRange();
845
846 if (ExactUnsignedCR.isEmptySet() || ExactSignedCR.isEmptySet()) {
847 EXPECT_TRUE(CR.isEmptySet());
848 return;
849 }
850
851 ConstantRange Exact = ExactSignedCR.intersectWith(ExactUnsignedCR);
852 EXPECT_EQ(Exact, CR);
853 });
854}

856TEST_F(ConstantRangeTest, AddWithNoWrap) {
857 typedef OverflowingBinaryOperator OBO;
858 EXPECT_EQ(Empty.addWithNoWrap(Some, OBO::NoSignedWrap), Empty);
859 EXPECT_EQ(Some.addWithNoWrap(Empty, OBO::NoSignedWrap), Empty);
860 EXPECT_EQ(Full.addWithNoWrap(Full, OBO::NoSignedWrap), Full);
861 EXPECT_NE(Full.addWithNoWrap(Some, OBO::NoSignedWrap), Full);
862 EXPECT_NE(Some.addWithNoWrap(Full, OBO::NoSignedWrap), Full);
863 EXPECT_EQ(Full.addWithNoWrap(ConstantRange(APInt(16, 1), APInt(16, 2)),
864 OBO::NoSignedWrap),
865 ConstantRange(APInt(16, INT16_MIN + 1), APInt(16, INT16_MIN)));
866 EXPECT_EQ(ConstantRange(APInt(16, 1), APInt(16, 2))
867 .addWithNoWrap(Full, OBO::NoSignedWrap),
868 ConstantRange(APInt(16, INT16_MIN + 1), APInt(16, INT16_MIN)));
869 EXPECT_EQ(Full.addWithNoWrap(ConstantRange(APInt(16, -1), APInt(16, 0)),
870 OBO::NoSignedWrap),
871 ConstantRange(APInt(16, INT16_MIN), APInt(16, INT16_MAX)));
872 EXPECT_EQ(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 100), APInt(8, 120))
873 .addWithNoWrap(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 120), APInt(8, 123)),
874 OBO::NoSignedWrap),
875 ConstantRange(8, false));
876 EXPECT_EQ(ConstantRange(APInt(8, -120), APInt(8, -100))
877 .addWithNoWrap(ConstantRange(APInt(8, -110), APInt(8, -100)),
878 OBO::NoSignedWrap),
879 ConstantRange(8, false));
880 EXPECT_EQ(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 0), APInt(8, 101))
881 .addWithNoWrap(ConstantRange(APInt(8, -128), APInt(8, 28)),
882 OBO::NoSignedWrap),
883 ConstantRange(8, true));
884 EXPECT_EQ(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 0), APInt(8, 101))
885 .addWithNoWrap(ConstantRange(APInt(8, -120), APInt(8, 29)),
886 OBO::NoSignedWrap),
887 ConstantRange(APInt(8, -120), APInt(8, -128)));
888 EXPECT_EQ(ConstantRange(APInt(8, -50), APInt(8, 50))
889 .addWithNoWrap(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 10), APInt(8, 20)),
890 OBO::NoSignedWrap),
891 ConstantRange(APInt(8, -40), APInt(8, 69)));
892 EXPECT_EQ(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 10), APInt(8, 20))
893 .addWithNoWrap(ConstantRange(APInt(8, -50), APInt(8, 50)),
894 OBO::NoSignedWrap),
895 ConstantRange(APInt(8, -40), APInt(8, 69)));
896 EXPECT_EQ(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 120), APInt(8, -10))
897 .addWithNoWrap(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 5), APInt(8, 20)),
898 OBO::NoSignedWrap),
899 ConstantRange(APInt(8, 125), APInt(8, 9)));
900 EXPECT_EQ(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 5), APInt(8, 20))
901 .addWithNoWrap(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 120), APInt(8, -10)),
902 OBO::NoSignedWrap),
903 ConstantRange(APInt(8, 125), APInt(8, 9)));
904
905 TestAddWithNoSignedWrapExhaustive(
906 [](const ConstantRange &CR1, const ConstantRange &CR2) {
907 return CR1.addWithNoWrap(CR2, OBO::NoSignedWrap);
908 },
909 [](bool &IsOverflow, const APInt &N1, const APInt &N2) {
910 return N1.sadd_ov(N2, IsOverflow);
911 });
912
913 EXPECT_EQ(Empty.addWithNoWrap(Some, OBO::NoUnsignedWrap), Empty);
914 EXPECT_EQ(Some.addWithNoWrap(Empty, OBO::NoUnsignedWrap), Empty);
915 EXPECT_EQ(Full.addWithNoWrap(Full, OBO::NoUnsignedWrap), Full);
916 EXPECT_NE(Full.addWithNoWrap(Some, OBO::NoUnsignedWrap), Full);
917 EXPECT_NE(Some.addWithNoWrap(Full, OBO::NoUnsignedWrap), Full);
918 EXPECT_EQ(Full.addWithNoWrap(ConstantRange(APInt(16, 1), APInt(16, 2)),
919 OBO::NoUnsignedWrap),
920 ConstantRange(APInt(16, 1), APInt(16, 0)));
921 EXPECT_EQ(ConstantRange(APInt(16, 1), APInt(16, 2))
922 .addWithNoWrap(Full, OBO::NoUnsignedWrap),
923 ConstantRange(APInt(16, 1), APInt(16, 0)));
924 EXPECT_EQ(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 200), APInt(8, 220))
925 .addWithNoWrap(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 100), APInt(8, 123)),
926 OBO::NoUnsignedWrap),
927 ConstantRange(8, false));
928 EXPECT_EQ(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 0), APInt(8, 101))
929 .addWithNoWrap(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 0), APInt(8, 156)),
930 OBO::NoUnsignedWrap),
931 ConstantRange(8, true));
932 EXPECT_EQ(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 0), APInt(8, 101))
933 .addWithNoWrap(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 10), APInt(8, 29)),
934 OBO::NoUnsignedWrap),
935 ConstantRange(APInt(8, 10), APInt(8, 129)));
936 EXPECT_EQ(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 20), APInt(8, 10))
937 .addWithNoWrap(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 50), APInt(8, 200)),
938 OBO::NoUnsignedWrap),
939 ConstantRange(APInt(8, 50), APInt(8, 0)));
940 EXPECT_EQ(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 10), APInt(8, 20))
941 .addWithNoWrap(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 50), APInt(8, 200)),
942 OBO::NoUnsignedWrap),
943 ConstantRange(APInt(8, 60), APInt(8, -37)));
944 EXPECT_EQ(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 20), APInt(8, -30))
945 .addWithNoWrap(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 5), APInt(8, 20)),
946 OBO::NoUnsignedWrap),
947 ConstantRange(APInt(8, 25), APInt(8, -11)));
948 EXPECT_EQ(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 5), APInt(8, 20))
949 .addWithNoWrap(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 20), APInt(8, -30)),
950 OBO::NoUnsignedWrap),
951 ConstantRange(APInt(8, 25), APInt(8, -11)));

953 TestAddWithNoUnsignedWrapExhaustive(
954 [](const ConstantRange &CR1, const ConstantRange &CR2) {

956 },
957 [](bool &IsOverflow, const APInt &N1, const APInt &N2) {

979 .addWithNoWrap(ConstantRange(APInt(8, 20), APInt(8, 30)),
980 OBO::NoUnsignedWrap),

1203TEST_F(ConstantRangeTest, SDiv) {
1204 unsigned Bits = 4;
1205 EnumerateTwoConstantRanges(Bits, [&](const ConstantRange &CR1,
1206 const ConstantRange &CR2) {
1207 // Collect possible results in a bit vector. We store the signed value plus
1208 // a bias to make it unsigned.
1209 int Bias = 1 << (Bits - 1);
1210 BitVector Results(1 << Bits);
1211 ForeachNumInConstantRange(CR1, [&](const APInt &N1) {
1212 ForeachNumInConstantRange(CR2, [&](const APInt &N2) {
1213 // Division by zero is UB.
1214 if (N2 == 0)
1215 return;
1216
1217 // SignedMin / -1 is UB.
1218 if (N1.isMinSignedValue() && N2.isAllOnesValue())
1219 return;
1220
1221 APInt N = N1.sdiv(N2);
1222 Results.set(N.getSExtValue() + Bias);
1223 });
1224 });
1225
1226 ConstantRange CR = CR1.sdiv(CR2);
1227 if (Results.none()) {
1228 EXPECT_TRUE(CR.isEmptySet());
1229 return;
1230 }
1231
1232 // If there is a non-full signed envelope, that should be the result.
1233 APInt SMin(Bits, Results.find_first() - Bias);
1234 APInt SMax(Bits, Results.find_last() - Bias);
1235 ConstantRange Envelope = ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(SMin, SMax + 1);
1236 if (!Envelope.isFullSet()) {
1237 EXPECT_EQ(Envelope, CR);
1238 return;
1239 }
1240
1241 // If the signed envelope is a full set, try to find a smaller sign wrapped
1242 // set that is separated in negative and positive components (or one which
1243 // can also additionally contain zero).
1244 int LastNeg = Results.find_last_in(0, Bias) - Bias;
1245 int LastPos = Results.find_next(Bias) - Bias;
1246 if (Results[Bias]) {
1247 if (LastNeg == -1)
1248 ++LastNeg;
1249 else if (LastPos == 1)
1250 --LastPos;
1251 }
1252
1253 APInt WMax(Bits, LastNeg);
1254 APInt WMin(Bits, LastPos);
1255 ConstantRange Wrapped = ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(WMin, WMax + 1);
1256 EXPECT_EQ(Wrapped, CR);
1257 });
1258}

1260TEST_F(ConstantRangeTest, URem) {
1261 EXPECT_EQ(Full.urem(Empty), Empty);
1262 EXPECT_EQ(Empty.urem(Full), Empty);
1263 // urem by zero is poison.
1264 EXPECT_EQ(Full.urem(ConstantRange(APInt(16, 0))), Empty);
1265 // urem by full range doesn't contain MaxValue.
1266 EXPECT_EQ(Full.urem(Full), ConstantRange(APInt(16, 0), APInt(16, 0xffff)));
1267 // urem is upper bounded by maximum RHS minus one.
1268 EXPECT_EQ(Full.urem(ConstantRange(APInt(16, 0), APInt(16, 123))),
1269 ConstantRange(APInt(16, 0), APInt(16, 122)));
1270 // urem is upper bounded by maximum LHS.
1271 EXPECT_EQ(ConstantRange(APInt(16, 0), APInt(16, 123)).urem(Full),
1272 ConstantRange(APInt(16, 0), APInt(16, 123)));
1273 // If the LHS is always lower than the RHS, the result is the LHS.
1274 EXPECT_EQ(ConstantRange(APInt(16, 10), APInt(16, 20))
1275 .urem(ConstantRange(APInt(16, 20), APInt(16, 30))),
1276 ConstantRange(APInt(16, 10), APInt(16, 20)));
1277 // It has to be strictly lower, otherwise the top value may wrap to zero.
1278 EXPECT_EQ(ConstantRange(APInt(16, 10), APInt(16, 20))
1279 .urem(ConstantRange(APInt(16, 19), APInt(16, 30))),
1280 ConstantRange(APInt(16, 0), APInt(16, 20)));
1281 // [12, 14] % 10 is [2, 4], but we conservatively compute [0, 9].
1282 EXPECT_EQ(ConstantRange(APInt(16, 12), APInt(16, 15))
1283 .urem(ConstantRange(APInt(16, 10))),
1284 ConstantRange(APInt(16, 0), APInt(16, 10)));
1285
1286 TestUnsignedBinOpExhaustive(
1287 [](const ConstantRange &CR1, const ConstantRange &CR2) {
1288 return CR1.urem(CR2);
1289 },
1290 [](const APInt &N1, const APInt &N2) {
1291 return N1.urem(N2);
1292 },
1293 /* SkipZeroRHS */ true, /* CorrectnessOnly */ true);
1294}

1296TEST_F(ConstantRangeTest, SRem) {
1297 EXPECT_EQ(Full.srem(Empty), Empty);
1298 EXPECT_EQ(Empty.srem(Full), Empty);
1299 // srem by zero is UB.
1300 EXPECT_EQ(Full.srem(ConstantRange(APInt(16, 0))), Empty);
1301 // srem by full range doesn't contain SignedMinValue.
1302 EXPECT_EQ(Full.srem(Full), ConstantRange(APInt::getSignedMinValue(16) + 1,
1303 APInt::getSignedMinValue(16)));
1304
1305 ConstantRange PosMod(APInt(16, 10), APInt(16, 21)); // [10, 20]
1306 ConstantRange NegMod(APInt(16, -20), APInt(16, -9)); // [-20, -10]
1307 ConstantRange IntMinMod(APInt::getSignedMinValue(16));
1308
1309 ConstantRange Expected(16, true);
1310
1311 // srem is bounded by abs(RHS) minus one.
1312 ConstantRange PosLargeLHS(APInt(16, 0), APInt(16, 41));
1313 Expected = ConstantRange(APInt(16, 0), APInt(16, 20));
1314 EXPECT_EQ(PosLargeLHS.srem(PosMod), Expected);
1315 EXPECT_EQ(PosLargeLHS.srem(NegMod), Expected);
1316 ConstantRange NegLargeLHS(APInt(16, -40), APInt(16, 1));
1317 Expected = ConstantRange(APInt(16, -19), APInt(16, 1));
1318 EXPECT_EQ(NegLargeLHS.srem(PosMod), Expected);
1319 EXPECT_EQ(NegLargeLHS.srem(NegMod), Expected);
1320 ConstantRange PosNegLargeLHS(APInt(16, -32), APInt(16, 38));
1321 Expected = ConstantRange(APInt(16, -19), APInt(16, 20));
1322 EXPECT_EQ(PosNegLargeLHS.srem(PosMod), Expected);
1323 EXPECT_EQ(PosNegLargeLHS.srem(NegMod), Expected);
1324
1325 // srem is bounded by LHS.
1326 ConstantRange PosLHS(APInt(16, 0), APInt(16, 16));
1327 EXPECT_EQ(PosLHS.srem(PosMod), PosLHS);
1328 EXPECT_EQ(PosLHS.srem(NegMod), PosLHS);
1329 EXPECT_EQ(PosLHS.srem(IntMinMod), PosLHS);
1330 ConstantRange NegLHS(APInt(16, -15), APInt(16, 1));
1331 EXPECT_EQ(NegLHS.srem(PosMod), NegLHS);
1332 EXPECT_EQ(NegLHS.srem(NegMod), NegLHS);
1333 EXPECT_EQ(NegLHS.srem(IntMinMod), NegLHS);
1334 ConstantRange PosNegLHS(APInt(16, -12), APInt(16, 18));
1335 EXPECT_EQ(PosNegLHS.srem(PosMod), PosNegLHS);
1336 EXPECT_EQ(PosNegLHS.srem(NegMod), PosNegLHS);
1337 EXPECT_EQ(PosNegLHS.srem(IntMinMod), PosNegLHS);
1338
1339 // srem is LHS if it is smaller than RHS.
1340 ConstantRange PosSmallLHS(APInt(16, 3), APInt(16, 8));
1341 EXPECT_EQ(PosSmallLHS.srem(PosMod), PosSmallLHS);
1342 EXPECT_EQ(PosSmallLHS.srem(NegMod), PosSmallLHS);
1343 EXPECT_EQ(PosSmallLHS.srem(IntMinMod), PosSmallLHS);
1344 ConstantRange NegSmallLHS(APInt(16, -7), APInt(16, -2));
1345 EXPECT_EQ(NegSmallLHS.srem(PosMod), NegSmallLHS);
1346 EXPECT_EQ(NegSmallLHS.srem(NegMod), NegSmallLHS);
1347 EXPECT_EQ(NegSmallLHS.srem(IntMinMod), NegSmallLHS);
1348 ConstantRange PosNegSmallLHS(APInt(16, -3), APInt(16, 8));
1349 EXPECT_EQ(PosNegSmallLHS.srem(PosMod), PosNegSmallLHS);
1350 EXPECT_EQ(PosNegSmallLHS.srem(NegMod), PosNegSmallLHS);
1351 EXPECT_EQ(PosNegSmallLHS.srem(IntMinMod), PosNegSmallLHS);
1352
1353 // Example of a suboptimal result:
1354 // [12, 14] srem 10 is [2, 4], but we conservatively compute [0, 9].
1355 EXPECT_EQ(ConstantRange(APInt(16, 12), APInt(16, 15))
1356 .srem(ConstantRange(APInt(16, 10))),
1357 ConstantRange(APInt(16, 0), APInt(16, 10)));
1358
1359 TestSignedBinOpExhaustive(
1360 [](const ConstantRange &CR1, const ConstantRange &CR2) {
1361 return CR1.srem(CR2);
1362 },
1363 [](const APInt &N1, const APInt &N2) {
1364 return N1.srem(N2);
1365 },
1366 /* SkipZeroRHS */ true, /* CorrectnessOnly */ true);
1367}

1501TEST(ConstantRange, MakeGuaranteedNoWrapRegion) {
1502 const int IntMin4Bits = 8;
1503 const int IntMax4Bits = 7;
1504 typedef OverflowingBinaryOperator OBO;
1505
1506 for (int Const : {0, -1, -2, 1, 2, IntMin4Bits, IntMax4Bits}) {
1507 APInt C(4, Const, true /* = isSigned */);
1508
1509 auto NUWRegion = ConstantRange::makeGuaranteedNoWrapRegion(
1510 Instruction::Add, C, OBO::NoUnsignedWrap);
1511
1512 EXPECT_FALSE(NUWRegion.isEmptySet());
1513
1514 auto NSWRegion = ConstantRange::makeGuaranteedNoWrapRegion(
1515 Instruction::Add, C, OBO::NoSignedWrap);
1516
1517 EXPECT_FALSE(NSWRegion.isEmptySet());
1518
1519 for (APInt I = NUWRegion.getLower(), E = NUWRegion.getUpper(); I != E;
1520 ++I) {
1521 bool Overflow = false;
1522 (void)I.uadd_ov(C, Overflow);
1523 EXPECT_FALSE(Overflow);
1524 }
1525
1526 for (APInt I = NSWRegion.getLower(), E = NSWRegion.getUpper(); I != E;
1527 ++I) {
1528 bool Overflow = false;
1529 (void)I.sadd_ov(C, Overflow);
1530 EXPECT_FALSE(Overflow);
1531 }
1532 }
1533
1534 for (int Const : {0, -1, -2, 1, 2, IntMin4Bits, IntMax4Bits}) {
1535 APInt C(4, Const, true /* = isSigned */);
1536
1537 auto NUWRegion = ConstantRange::makeGuaranteedNoWrapRegion(
1538 Instruction::Sub, C, OBO::NoUnsignedWrap);
1539
1540 EXPECT_FALSE(NUWRegion.isEmptySet());
1541
1542 auto NSWRegion = ConstantRange::makeGuaranteedNoWrapRegion(
1543 Instruction::Sub, C, OBO::NoSignedWrap);
1544
1545 EXPECT_FALSE(NSWRegion.isEmptySet());
1546
1547 for (APInt I = NUWRegion.getLower(), E = NUWRegion.getUpper(); I != E;
1548 ++I) {
1549 bool Overflow = false;
1550 (void)I.usub_ov(C, Overflow);
1551 EXPECT_FALSE(Overflow);
1552 }
1553
1554 for (APInt I = NSWRegion.getLower(), E = NSWRegion.getUpper(); I != E;
1555 ++I) {
1556 bool Overflow = false;
1557 (void)I.ssub_ov(C, Overflow);
1558 EXPECT_FALSE(Overflow);
1559 }
1560 }
1561
1562 auto NSWForAllValues = ConstantRange::makeGuaranteedNoWrapRegion(
1563 Instruction::Add, ConstantRange(32, /* isFullSet = */ true),
1564 OBO::NoSignedWrap);
1565 EXPECT_TRUE(NSWForAllValues.isSingleElement() &&
1566 NSWForAllValues.getSingleElement()->isMinValue());
1567
1568 NSWForAllValues = ConstantRange::makeGuaranteedNoWrapRegion(
1569 Instruction::Sub, ConstantRange(32, /* isFullSet = */ true),
1570 OBO::NoSignedWrap);
1571 EXPECT_TRUE(NSWForAllValues.isSingleElement() &&
1572 NSWForAllValues.getSingleElement()->isMaxValue());
1573
1574 auto NUWForAllValues = ConstantRange::makeGuaranteedNoWrapRegion(
1575 Instruction::Add, ConstantRange(32, /* isFullSet = */ true),
1576 OBO::NoUnsignedWrap);
1577 EXPECT_TRUE(NUWForAllValues.isSingleElement() &&
1578 NUWForAllValues.getSingleElement()->isMinValue());
1579
1580 NUWForAllValues = ConstantRange::makeGuaranteedNoWrapRegion(
1581 Instruction::Sub, ConstantRange(32, /* isFullSet = */ true),
1582 OBO::NoUnsignedWrap);
1583 EXPECT_TRUE(NUWForAllValues.isSingleElement() &&
1584 NUWForAllValues.getSingleElement()->isMaxValue());
1585
1586 EXPECT_TRUE(ConstantRange::makeGuaranteedNoWrapRegion(
1587 Instruction::Add, APInt(32, 0), OBO::NoUnsignedWrap).isFullSet());
1588 EXPECT_TRUE(ConstantRange::makeGuaranteedNoWrapRegion(
1589 Instruction::Add, APInt(32, 0), OBO::NoSignedWrap).isFullSet());
1590 EXPECT_TRUE(ConstantRange::makeGuaranteedNoWrapRegion(
1591 Instruction::Sub, APInt(32, 0), OBO::NoUnsignedWrap).isFullSet());
1592 EXPECT_TRUE(ConstantRange::makeGuaranteedNoWrapRegion(
1593 Instruction::Sub, APInt(32, 0), OBO::NoSignedWrap).isFullSet());
1594

1700 OBO::NoUnsignedWrap),

1723
1724template<typename Fn>
1725void TestNoWrapRegionExhaustive(Instruction::BinaryOps BinOp,
1726 unsigned NoWrapKind, Fn OverflowFn) {
1727 unsigned Bits = 5;
1728 EnumerateConstantRanges(Bits, [&](const ConstantRange &CR) {
1729 if (CR.isEmptySet())
1730 return;
1731 if (Instruction::isShift(BinOp) && CR.getUnsignedMax().uge(Bits))
1732 return;
1733
1734 ConstantRange NoWrap =
1735 ConstantRange::makeGuaranteedNoWrapRegion(BinOp, CR, NoWrapKind);
1736 ConstantRange Full = ConstantRange::getFull(Bits);
1737 ForeachNumInConstantRange(Full, [&](const APInt &N1) {
1738 bool NoOverflow = true;
1739 bool Overflow = true;
1740 ForeachNumInConstantRange(CR, [&](const APInt &N2) {
1741 if (OverflowFn(N1, N2))
1742 NoOverflow = false;
1743 else
1744 Overflow = false;
1745 });
1746 EXPECT_EQ(NoOverflow, NoWrap.contains(N1));
1747
1748 // The no-wrap range is exact for single-element ranges.
1749 if (CR.isSingleElement()) {
1750 EXPECT_EQ(Overflow, !NoWrap.contains(N1));
1751 }
1752 });
1753 });
1754}
1755
1756// Show that makeGuaranteedNoWrapRegion() is maximal, and for single-element
1757// ranges also exact.
1758TEST(ConstantRange, NoWrapRegionExhaustive) {
1759 TestNoWrapRegionExhaustive(
1760 Instruction::Add, OverflowingBinaryOperator::NoUnsignedWrap,
1761 [](const APInt &N1, const APInt &N2) {
1762 bool Overflow;
1763 (void) N1.uadd_ov(N2, Overflow);
1764 return Overflow;
1765 });
1766 TestNoWrapRegionExhaustive(
1767 Instruction::Add, OverflowingBinaryOperator::NoSignedWrap,
1768 [](const APInt &N1, const APInt &N2) {
1769 bool Overflow;
1770 (void) N1.sadd_ov(N2, Overflow);
1771 return Overflow;
1772 });
1773 TestNoWrapRegionExhaustive(
1774 Instruction::Sub, OverflowingBinaryOperator::NoUnsignedWrap,
1775 [](const APInt &N1, const APInt &N2) {
1776 bool Overflow;
1777 (void) N1.usub_ov(N2, Overflow);
1778 return Overflow;
1779 });
1780 TestNoWrapRegionExhaustive(
1781 Instruction::Sub, OverflowingBinaryOperator::NoSignedWrap,
1782 [](const APInt &N1, const APInt &N2) {
1783 bool Overflow;
1784 (void) N1.ssub_ov(N2, Overflow);
1785 return Overflow;
1786 });
1787 TestNoWrapRegionExhaustive(
1788 Instruction::Mul, OverflowingBinaryOperator::NoUnsignedWrap,
1789 [](const APInt &N1, const APInt &N2) {
1790 bool Overflow;
1791 (void) N1.umul_ov(N2, Overflow);
1792 return Overflow;
1793 });
1794 TestNoWrapRegionExhaustive(
1795 Instruction::Mul, OverflowingBinaryOperator::NoSignedWrap,
1796 [](const APInt &N1, const APInt &N2) {
1797 bool Overflow;
1798 (void) N1.smul_ov(N2, Overflow);
1799 return Overflow;
1800 });
1801 TestNoWrapRegionExhaustive(Instruction::Shl,
1802 OverflowingBinaryOperator::NoUnsignedWrap,
1803 [](const APInt &N1, const APInt &N2) {
1804 bool Overflow;
1805 (void)N1.ushl_ov(N2, Overflow);
1806 return Overflow;
1807 });
1808 TestNoWrapRegionExhaustive(Instruction::Shl,
1809 OverflowingBinaryOperator::NoSignedWrap,
1810 [](const APInt &N1, const APInt &N2) {
1811 bool Overflow;
1812 (void)N1.sshl_ov(N2, Overflow);
1813 return Overflow;
1814 });
1815}

1817TEST(ConstantRange, GetEquivalentICmp) {
1818 APInt RHS;
1819 CmpInst::Predicate Pred;
1820
1821 EXPECT_TRUE(ConstantRange(APInt::getMinValue(32), APInt(32, 100))
1822 .getEquivalentICmp(Pred, RHS));
1823 EXPECT_EQ(Pred, CmpInst::ICMP_ULT);
1824 EXPECT_EQ(RHS, APInt(32, 100));
1825
1826 EXPECT_TRUE(ConstantRange(APInt::getSignedMinValue(32), APInt(32, 100))
1827 .getEquivalentICmp(Pred, RHS));
1828 EXPECT_EQ(Pred, CmpInst::ICMP_SLT);
1829 EXPECT_EQ(RHS, APInt(32, 100));
1830
1831 EXPECT_TRUE(ConstantRange(APInt(32, 100), APInt::getMinValue(32))
1832 .getEquivalentICmp(Pred, RHS));
1833 EXPECT_EQ(Pred, CmpInst::ICMP_UGE);
1834 EXPECT_EQ(RHS, APInt(32, 100));
1835
1836 EXPECT_TRUE(ConstantRange(APInt(32, 100), APInt::getSignedMinValue(32))
1837 .getEquivalentICmp(Pred, RHS));
1838 EXPECT_EQ(Pred, CmpInst::ICMP_SGE);
1839 EXPECT_EQ(RHS, APInt(32, 100));
1840
1841 EXPECT_TRUE(
1842 ConstantRange(32, /*isFullSet=*/true).getEquivalentICmp(Pred, RHS));
1843 EXPECT_EQ(Pred, CmpInst::ICMP_UGE);
1844 EXPECT_EQ(RHS, APInt(32, 0));
1845
1846 EXPECT_TRUE(
1847 ConstantRange(32, /*isFullSet=*/false).getEquivalentICmp(Pred, RHS));
1848 EXPECT_EQ(Pred, CmpInst::ICMP_ULT);
1849 EXPECT_EQ(RHS, APInt(32, 0));
1850
1851 EXPECT_FALSE(ConstantRange(APInt(32, 100), APInt(32, 200))
1852 .getEquivalentICmp(Pred, RHS));
1853
1854 EXPECT_FALSE(ConstantRange(APInt::getSignedMinValue(32) - APInt(32, 100),
1855 APInt::getSignedMinValue(32) + APInt(32, 100))
1856 .getEquivalentICmp(Pred, RHS));
1857
1858 EXPECT_FALSE(ConstantRange(APInt::getMinValue(32) - APInt(32, 100),
1859 APInt::getMinValue(32) + APInt(32, 100))
1860 .getEquivalentICmp(Pred, RHS));
1861
1862 EXPECT_TRUE(ConstantRange(APInt(32, 100)).getEquivalentICmp(Pred, RHS));
1863 EXPECT_EQ(Pred, CmpInst::ICMP_EQ);
1864 EXPECT_EQ(RHS, APInt(32, 100));
1865
1866 EXPECT_TRUE(
1867 ConstantRange(APInt(32, 100)).inverse().getEquivalentICmp(Pred, RHS));
1868 EXPECT_EQ(Pred, CmpInst::ICMP_NE);
1869 EXPECT_EQ(RHS, APInt(32, 100));
1870
1871 EXPECT_TRUE(
1872 ConstantRange(APInt(512, 100)).inverse().getEquivalentICmp(Pred, RHS));
1873 EXPECT_EQ(Pred, CmpInst::ICMP_NE);
1874 EXPECT_EQ(RHS, APInt(512, 100));
1875
1876 // NB! It would be correct for the following four calls to getEquivalentICmp
1877 // to return ordered predicates like CmpInst::ICMP_ULT or CmpInst::ICMP_UGT.
1878 // However, that's not the case today.
1879
1880 EXPECT_TRUE(ConstantRange(APInt(32, 0)).getEquivalentICmp(Pred, RHS));
1881 EXPECT_EQ(Pred, CmpInst::ICMP_EQ);
1882 EXPECT_EQ(RHS, APInt(32, 0));
1883
1884 EXPECT_TRUE(
1885 ConstantRange(APInt(32, 0)).inverse().getEquivalentICmp(Pred, RHS));
1886 EXPECT_EQ(Pred, CmpInst::ICMP_NE);
1887 EXPECT_EQ(RHS, APInt(32, 0));
1888
1889 EXPECT_TRUE(ConstantRange(APInt(32, -1)).getEquivalentICmp(Pred, RHS));
1890 EXPECT_EQ(Pred, CmpInst::ICMP_EQ);
1891 EXPECT_EQ(RHS, APInt(32, -1));
1892
1893 EXPECT_TRUE(
1894 ConstantRange(APInt(32, -1)).inverse().getEquivalentICmp(Pred, RHS));
1895 EXPECT_EQ(Pred, CmpInst::ICMP_NE);
1896 EXPECT_EQ(RHS, APInt(32, -1));
1897}

1899#define EXPECT_MAY_OVERFLOW(op) \
1900 EXPECT_EQ(ConstantRange::OverflowResult::MayOverflow, (op))
1901#define EXPECT_ALWAYS_OVERFLOWS_LOW(op) \
1902 EXPECT_EQ(ConstantRange::OverflowResult::AlwaysOverflowsLow, (op))
1903#define EXPECT_ALWAYS_OVERFLOWS_HIGH(op) \
1904 EXPECT_EQ(ConstantRange::OverflowResult::AlwaysOverflowsHigh, (op))
1905#define EXPECT_NEVER_OVERFLOWS(op) \
1906 EXPECT_EQ(ConstantRange::OverflowResult::NeverOverflows, (op))
1907
1908TEST_F(ConstantRangeTest, UnsignedAddOverflow) {
1909 // Ill-defined - may overflow is a conservative result.
1910 EXPECT_MAY_OVERFLOW(Some.unsignedAddMayOverflow(Empty));
1911 EXPECT_MAY_OVERFLOW(Empty.unsignedAddMayOverflow(Some));
1912
1913 // Never overflow despite one full/wrap set.
1914 ConstantRange Zero(APInt::getNullValue(16));
1915 EXPECT_NEVER_OVERFLOWS(Full.unsignedAddMayOverflow(Zero));
1916 EXPECT_NEVER_OVERFLOWS(Wrap.unsignedAddMayOverflow(Zero));
1917 EXPECT_NEVER_OVERFLOWS(Zero.unsignedAddMayOverflow(Full));
1918 EXPECT_NEVER_OVERFLOWS(Zero.unsignedAddMayOverflow(Wrap));
1919
1920 // But usually full/wrap always may overflow.
1921 EXPECT_MAY_OVERFLOW(Full.unsignedAddMayOverflow(One));
1922 EXPECT_MAY_OVERFLOW(Wrap.unsignedAddMayOverflow(One));
1923 EXPECT_MAY_OVERFLOW(One.unsignedAddMayOverflow(Full));
1924 EXPECT_MAY_OVERFLOW(One.unsignedAddMayOverflow(Wrap));
1925
1926 ConstantRange A(APInt(16, 0xfd00), APInt(16, 0xfe00));
1927 ConstantRange B1(APInt(16, 0x0100), APInt(16, 0x0201));
1928 ConstantRange B2(APInt(16, 0x0100), APInt(16, 0x0202));
1929 EXPECT_NEVER_OVERFLOWS(A.unsignedAddMayOverflow(B1));
1930 EXPECT_MAY_OVERFLOW(A.unsignedAddMayOverflow(B2));
1931 EXPECT_NEVER_OVERFLOWS(B1.unsignedAddMayOverflow(A));
1932 EXPECT_MAY_OVERFLOW(B2.unsignedAddMayOverflow(A));
1933
1934 ConstantRange C1(APInt(16, 0x0299), APInt(16, 0x0400));
1935 ConstantRange C2(APInt(16, 0x0300), APInt(16, 0x0400));
1936 EXPECT_MAY_OVERFLOW(A.unsignedAddMayOverflow(C1));
1937 EXPECT_ALWAYS_OVERFLOWS_HIGH(A.unsignedAddMayOverflow(C2));
1938 EXPECT_MAY_OVERFLOW(C1.unsignedAddMayOverflow(A));
1939 EXPECT_ALWAYS_OVERFLOWS_HIGH(C2.unsignedAddMayOverflow(A));
1940}

2055 ConstantRange C(APInt(16, 0x8200), APInt(16, 0x8300));
2056 ConstantRange D1(APInt(16, 0x0100), APInt(16, 0x0201));
2057 ConstantRange D2(APInt(16, 0x0100), APInt(16, 0x0202));
2058 EXPECT_NEVER_OVERFLOWS(C.signedSubMayOverflow(D1));
2059 EXPECT_MAY_OVERFLOW(C.signedSubMayOverflow(D2));
2060 ConstantRange D3(APInt(16, 0x0299), APInt(16, 0x0400));
2061 ConstantRange D4(APInt(16, 0x0300), APInt(16, 0x0400));
2062 EXPECT_MAY_OVERFLOW(C.signedSubMayOverflow(D3));
2063 EXPECT_ALWAYS_OVERFLOWS_LOW(C.signedSubMayOverflow(D4));
2064
2065 ConstantRange E(APInt(16, 0xff00), APInt(16, 0x0100));
2066 EXPECT_NEVER_OVERFLOWS(E.signedSubMayOverflow(E));
2067 ConstantRange F(APInt(16, 0xf000), APInt(16, 0x7001));
2068 EXPECT_MAY_OVERFLOW(F.signedSubMayOverflow(F));
2069}
2070
2071template<typename Fn1, typename Fn2>
2072static void TestOverflowExhaustive(Fn1 OverflowFn, Fn2 MayOverflowFn) {
2073 // Constant range overflow checks are tested exhaustively on 4-bit numbers.
2074 unsigned Bits = 4;
2075 EnumerateTwoConstantRanges(Bits, [=](const ConstantRange &CR1,
2076 const ConstantRange &CR2) {
2077 // Loop over all N1 in CR1 and N2 in CR2 and check whether any of the
2078 // operations have overflow / have no overflow.
2079 bool RangeHasOverflowLow = false;
2080 bool RangeHasOverflowHigh = false;
2081 bool RangeHasNoOverflow = false;
2082 ForeachNumInConstantRange(CR1, [&](const APInt &N1) {
2083 ForeachNumInConstantRange(CR2, [&](const APInt &N2) {
2084 bool IsOverflowHigh;
2085 if (!OverflowFn(IsOverflowHigh, N1, N2)) {
2086 RangeHasNoOverflow = true;
2087 return;
2088 }
2089
2090 if (IsOverflowHigh)
2091 RangeHasOverflowHigh = true;
2092 else
2093 RangeHasOverflowLow = true;
2094 });
2095 });
2096
2097 ConstantRange::OverflowResult OR = MayOverflowFn(CR1, CR2);
2098 switch (OR) {
2099 case ConstantRange::OverflowResult::AlwaysOverflowsLow:
2100 EXPECT_TRUE(RangeHasOverflowLow);
2101 EXPECT_FALSE(RangeHasOverflowHigh);
2102 EXPECT_FALSE(RangeHasNoOverflow);
2103 break;
2104 case ConstantRange::OverflowResult::AlwaysOverflowsHigh:
2105 EXPECT_TRUE(RangeHasOverflowHigh);
2106 EXPECT_FALSE(RangeHasOverflowLow);
2107 EXPECT_FALSE(RangeHasNoOverflow);
2108 break;
2109 case ConstantRange::OverflowResult::NeverOverflows:
2110 EXPECT_FALSE(RangeHasOverflowLow);
2111 EXPECT_FALSE(RangeHasOverflowHigh);
2112 EXPECT_TRUE(RangeHasNoOverflow);
2113 break;
2114 case ConstantRange::OverflowResult::MayOverflow:
2115 // We return MayOverflow for empty sets as a conservative result,
2116 // but of course neither the RangeHasOverflow nor the
2117 // RangeHasNoOverflow flags will be set.
2118 if (CR1.isEmptySet() || CR2.isEmptySet())
2119 break;
2120
2121 EXPECT_TRUE(RangeHasOverflowLow || RangeHasOverflowHigh);
2122 EXPECT_TRUE(RangeHasNoOverflow);
2123 break;
2124 }
2125 });
2126}

2133 IsOverflowHigh = true;
2134 return Overflow;

2136 [](const ConstantRange &CR1, const ConstantRange &CR2) {

2193TEST_F(ConstantRangeTest, FromKnownBits) {
2194 KnownBits Unknown(16);
2195 EXPECT_EQ(Full, ConstantRange::fromKnownBits(Unknown, /*signed*/false));
2196 EXPECT_EQ(Full, ConstantRange::fromKnownBits(Unknown, /*signed*/true));
2197
2198 // .10..01. -> unsigned 01000010 (66) to 11011011 (219)
2199 // -> signed 11000010 (194) to 01011011 (91)
2200 KnownBits Known(8);
2201 Known.Zero = 36;
2202 Known.One = 66;
2203 ConstantRange Unsigned(APInt(8, 66), APInt(8, 219 + 1));
2204 ConstantRange Signed(APInt(8, 194), APInt(8, 91 + 1));
2205 EXPECT_EQ(Unsigned, ConstantRange::fromKnownBits(Known, /*signed*/false));
2206 EXPECT_EQ(Signed, ConstantRange::fromKnownBits(Known, /*signed*/true));
2207
2208 // 1.10.10. -> 10100100 (164) to 11101101 (237)
2209 Known.Zero = 18;
2210 Known.One = 164;
2211 ConstantRange CR1(APInt(8, 164), APInt(8, 237 + 1));
2212 EXPECT_EQ(CR1, ConstantRange::fromKnownBits(Known, /*signed*/false));
2213 EXPECT_EQ(CR1, ConstantRange::fromKnownBits(Known, /*signed*/true));
2214
2215 // 01.0.1.0 -> 01000100 (68) to 01101110 (110)
2216 Known.Zero = 145;
2217 Known.One = 68;
2218 ConstantRange CR2(APInt(8, 68), APInt(8, 110 + 1));
2219 EXPECT_EQ(CR2, ConstantRange::fromKnownBits(Known, /*signed*/false));
2220 EXPECT_EQ(CR2, ConstantRange::fromKnownBits(Known, /*signed*/true));
2221}

2223TEST_F(ConstantRangeTest, FromKnownBitsExhaustive) {
2224 unsigned Bits = 4;
2225 unsigned Max = 1 << Bits;
2226 KnownBits Known(Bits);
2227 for (unsigned Zero = 0; Zero < Max; ++Zero) {
2228 for (unsigned One = 0; One < Max; ++One) {
2229 Known.Zero = Zero;
2230 Known.One = One;
2231 if (Known.hasConflict() || Known.isUnknown())
2232 continue;
2233
2234 UnsignedOpRangeGatherer UR(Bits);
2235 SignedOpRangeGatherer SR(Bits);
2236 for (unsigned N = 0; N < Max; ++N) {
2237 APInt Num(Bits, N);
2238 if ((Num & Known.Zero) != 0 || (~Num & Known.One) != 0)
2239 continue;
2240
2241 UR.account(Num);
2242 SR.account(Num);
2243 }
2244
2245 ConstantRange UnsignedCR = UR.getRange();
2246 ConstantRange SignedCR = SR.getRange();
2247 EXPECT_EQ(UnsignedCR, ConstantRange::fromKnownBits(Known, false));
2248 EXPECT_EQ(SignedCR, ConstantRange::fromKnownBits(Known, true));
2249 }
2250 }

2253TEST_F(ConstantRangeTest, Negative) {
2254 // All elements in an empty set (of which there are none) are both negative
2255 // and non-negative. Empty & full sets checked explicitly for clarity, but
2256 // they are also covered by the exhaustive test below.
2257 EXPECT_TRUE(Empty.isAllNegative());
2258 EXPECT_TRUE(Empty.isAllNonNegative());
2259 EXPECT_FALSE(Full.isAllNegative());
2260 EXPECT_FALSE(Full.isAllNonNegative());
2261
2262 unsigned Bits = 4;
2263 EnumerateConstantRanges(Bits, [](const ConstantRange &CR) {
2264 bool AllNegative = true;
2265 bool AllNonNegative = true;
2266 ForeachNumInConstantRange(CR, [&](const APInt &N) {
2267 if (!N.isNegative())
2268 AllNegative = false;
2269 if (!N.isNonNegative())
2270 AllNonNegative = false;
2271 });
2272 assert((CR.isEmptySet() || !AllNegative || !AllNonNegative) &&
2273 "Only empty set can be both all negative and all non-negative");
2274
2275 EXPECT_EQ(AllNegative, CR.isAllNegative());
2276 EXPECT_EQ(AllNonNegative, CR.isAllNonNegative());
2277 });
2278}

2365TEST_F(ConstantRangeTest, castOps) {
2366 ConstantRange A(APInt(16, 66), APInt(16, 128));
2367 ConstantRange FpToI8 = A.castOp(Instruction::FPToSI, 8);
2368 EXPECT_EQ(8u, FpToI8.getBitWidth());
2369 EXPECT_TRUE(FpToI8.isFullSet());
2370
2371 ConstantRange FpToI16 = A.castOp(Instruction::FPToSI, 16);
2372 EXPECT_EQ(16u, FpToI16.getBitWidth());
2373 EXPECT_EQ(A, FpToI16);
2374
2375 ConstantRange FPExtToDouble = A.castOp(Instruction::FPExt, 64);
2376 EXPECT_EQ(64u, FPExtToDouble.getBitWidth());
2377 EXPECT_TRUE(FPExtToDouble.isFullSet());
2378
2379 ConstantRange PtrToInt = A.castOp(Instruction::PtrToInt, 64);
2380 EXPECT_EQ(64u, PtrToInt.getBitWidth());
2381 EXPECT_TRUE(PtrToInt.isFullSet());
2382
2383 ConstantRange IntToPtr = A.castOp(Instruction::IntToPtr, 64);
2384 EXPECT_EQ(64u, IntToPtr.getBitWidth());
2385 EXPECT_TRUE(IntToPtr.isFullSet());

2388TEST_F(ConstantRangeTest, binaryXor) {
2389 // Single element ranges.
2390 ConstantRange R16(APInt(8, 16));
2391 ConstantRange R20(APInt(8, 20));
2392 EXPECT_EQ(*R16.binaryXor(R16).getSingleElement(), APInt(8, 0));
2393 EXPECT_EQ(*R16.binaryXor(R20).getSingleElement(), APInt(8, 16 ^ 20));
2394
2395 // Ranges with more than a single element. Handled conservatively for now.
2396 ConstantRange R16_35(APInt(8, 16), APInt(8, 35));
2397 ConstantRange R0_99(APInt(8, 0), APInt(8, 99));
2398 EXPECT_TRUE(R16_35.binaryXor(R16_35).isFullSet());
2399 EXPECT_TRUE(R16_35.binaryXor(R0_99).isFullSet());
2400 EXPECT_TRUE(R0_99.binaryXor(R16_35).isFullSet());
2401}
